        <div class="comment" id="comment-47773673">
  <div class="comment_head"><a href="/user/bmitch3020">bmitch3020</a> 13 hours ago</div>
  <div class="comment_text">I don&#x27;t want to stop Flock the company. I want to stop Flock the business model, along with all the other mass surveillance, and the data brokers. If the business models can&#x27;t be made illegal, it should at least come with liabilities so high that no sane business would want to hold data that is essentially toxic waste.<p>Without that, we are quickly spiraling into the dystopia where privacy is gone, and when the wrong person gets access to the data, entire populations are threatened.</div>
