<div class="comment" id="comment-47774165">
  <div class="comment_head"><a href="/user/otterley">otterley</a> 12 hours ago</div>
  <div class="comment_text">Why do people consistently and falsely believe that they have privacy in public settings? You are literally out in public. If you don&#x27;t want your behavior in public to be observed, then either don&#x27;t behave in such a way that you wouldn&#x27;t want observed, or stay home.<p>UPDATE: don&#x27;t conflate stalking with observation. These are not the same. You can observe, but you cannot intimidate.</div>
